- Not sure how relevant this is for the hyprland plugins loading.
  We currently use udis86 1.7.2 from https://github.com/vmt/udis86. debian and
  ubuntu have moved on to a more popular fork (which was what was bundled).
  Maybe we can file a BZ and ask:
  
  ```
  Currently the package is pointing to https://github.com/vmt/udis86 which has
  not been touched in 12 years or so.

  Would it be possible to switch to a more maintained fork (which is also not
  crazy active, but seems to be relatively popular):
  https://github.com/canihavesomecoffee/udis86 (cmake, pkg-config, library
  support, etc) ?

  Debian & Ubuntu already switched to that fork:
  https://packages.debian.org/sid/libudis86-0
  ```

